claude
______

# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer so slick,
Whose moves were incredibly quick.
    In bell bottoms wide,
    With remarkable stride,
He hustled and spun 'round the brick.

A lady with platform heels tall,
Was queen of the glittering ball.
    As lights flashed about,
    She'd twirl and shout out,
"The night isn't over, y'all!"

The DJ with records galore,
Kept everyone glued to the floor.
    With Bee Gees and more,
    He made booties soar,
Till dawn broke and they begged for encore.

deepseek
________

**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dance floor so bright,  
Where folks boogied all through the night.  
With mirror balls high,  
They’d shimmy and fly—  
Oh, disco was pure dynamite!  

The bass line would thump with a groove,  
And no one could possibly move.  
In platforms so tall,  
They’d strut down the hall,  
Then spin like they’d something to prove!  

But fashion soon faded from view,  
Though some still crave glitter and blue.  
So crank up the beat,  
And move those swift feet—  
Disco lives on in a few!

gemini
______

The Bee Gees, with falsetto so high,
Made disco ignite in the sky.
With glitter and flair,
On the dance floor to share,
A boogie that made spirits fly.

The mirror ball spun round and round,
To a beat that was funky and sound.
Platform shoes tall,
We gave it our all,
'Til the dawn on the dance floor was found.

Though tastes may now shift and evolve,
Disco's still got a passionate solve.
For a night full of fun,
'Til the morning has come,
And memories forever resolve.



